Programming for Robotics – Project Pitch
Project Title:
Smart Hazard Detection System
Group Members:
•	Ayush Patel (s5353051) 
•	Mohammad Rashed Khan (s5404089) 
•	Lachlan Roche (s542960) 
Target Specialisation:
Option A – Embedded Intelligence (Wokwi)
1. Executive Summary
The Smart Hazard Detection System is an embedded intelligent system designed to monitor environmental conditions and detect hazardous situations in real time. It is suitable for high-risk environments such as industrial facilities and fire-prone zones where early detection is critical.
The system integrates multiple sensors and applies sensor fusion with multi-condition decision logic to classify conditions into safe, warning, and emergency states. Based on these conditions, the system responds through visual, auditory, and physical outputs, ensuring a responsive and context-aware monitoring solution.
2. System Architecture (Sense–Think–Act)
Sensing (Inputs):
•	DHT22 Sensor: Measures temperature and humidity 
•	Ultrasonic Sensor: Detects nearby objects and environmental presence 
Processing (Thinking):
•	Finite State Machine (FSM): Controls system behaviour using structured states 
•	Decision Logic: Uses multi-condition evaluation combining temperature and humidity (sensor fusion) 
Actuation (Outputs):
•	Servo Motor: Performs scanning (0°–180°) 
•	LED Indicator: Green (Safe), Yellow (Warning), Red (Emergency) 
•	Buzzer: Provides alert signals during hazard conditions 
3. Behavioural Logic (Finite State Machine)
The system implements a 5-state FSM to ensure structured and adaptive behaviour:
State	Trigger Condition	Behaviour
IDLE	Safe conditions	Green LED, low monitoring
SURVEY	Periodic timer	Servo scanning, active sensing
CAUTION	Temp > 45°C OR Humidity < 20%	Yellow LED, intermittent buzzer
EMERGENCY	Temp > 60°C AND Humidity < 15%	Red LED blinking, continuous buzzer
FAILSAFE	Sensor error / invalid data	Safe mode, restricted outputs
This structure ensures multi-condition logic, clear transitions, and stable operation.
4. Specialisation: Embedded Intelligence
The system demonstrates embedded intelligence through:
•	Sensor Fusion: Uses combined temperature and humidity for hazard detection 
•	Context-Aware Behaviour: Adjusts system response based on severity 
•	Real-Time Logic: Continuously monitors and reacts without delay-based blocking 
5. Safety, Robustness & Reliability
The system includes:
•	Fail-safe mechanism: Handles sensor errors and invalid readings 
•	Controlled FSM behaviour: Prevents unpredictable system states 
•	Emergency alerts: Immediate visual and auditory response 
6. Advanced Component (10%)
The system includes adaptive behaviour by:
•	Adjusting alert intensity based on hazard level 
•	Increasing monitoring frequency during critical conditions 
•	Implementing intelligent scanning using servo motion

